    {
        "text": "How does this look? I'm basically holding the centroid of the fingers immobile as I zoom. So the top-left of the viewport is constantly adjusted by centroid\/oldzoom - centroid\/newzoom. Does this seem like the best approach?\n\n(I considered weighting by the finger that is moving more, but convinced myself I get that effect for free since the above adjustment is constantly happening as the fingers move.  But perhaps I'm rationalizing.)",
